# 🌟 5. Hidden Files Special Case

```bash id="pvn73e"
ls *
```

❌ Does NOT show hidden files

```bash id="k2z9s1"
ls .*     # shows hidden files
```

---

# 🌟 6. Escaping Wildcards

If you want literal `*` or `?`:

```bash id="8g9q9c"
ls \*.txt
```

---

# ⚡ Quick Cheat Sheet

* `*` → any number of characters
* `?` → exactly one character
* `[abc]` → match a, b, or c
* `[a-z]` → range
* `[!abc]` → NOT a, b, c

